 a = k\cdot(m^2 - n^2)   ,\ \, b = k\cdot(2mn) ,\ \, c = k\cdot(m^2 + n^2)\\ \implies b=2^n\\ \implies mnk=2^{n-1}\\ \implies k=\dfrac{2^{n-1}}{mn}
a=\dfrac{2^{n-1}}{mn}\cdot(m^2 - n^2)=\dfrac{2^{n-1}m}{n}-\dfrac{2^{n-1}n}{m}\\ \implies b=\dfrac{2^{n-1}m}{n}+\dfrac{2^{n-1}n}{m}
